@page "/faq"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>FAQ</PageTitle>

<div class="faq-page">
    <div class="faq-header">
        <h1 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="faq-subtitle">Quick answers about accounts, privacy, billing, and support.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="topic">
        <h2 class="topic-title">Account and access</h2>

        <div class="qa-grid">
            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>Do I need an account to use Museek?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Yes. An account is required to save songs, create playlists, and keep your library synced to your profile.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>How do I sign up, log in, and log out?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Use the Sign Up page to create an account. Use Log In to access your library. Use Log Out from your profile or navigation menu to end the session.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>I forgot my password. How do I reset it?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    On the Log In screen, select Forgot Password, then follow the email instructions. If you do not receive an email, check spam or try again with the correct address.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>How do I delete my account?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Go to Account Settings and choose Delete Account. This removes your profile and your personal library. Some logs may be kept briefly for security and auditing.
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="topic">
        <h2 class="topic-title">Privacy and safety</h2>

        <div class="qa-grid">
            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>Who can see my playlists?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    By default, your playlists are visible only to you. If sharing is introduced later, you will be able to control visibility per playlist.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>Are my liked songs private?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Yes. Your liked songs are tied to your account and are not shown publicly.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>Do you share my data with others?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    We do not sell your personal data. We only share data if required for essential service operations, legal requests, or security investigations.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>How do I report an issue or abuse?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Use the Support or Contact link in the footer. Include what happened, where it happened, and any screenshots. For urgent security issues, mark your message as Security.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>How do I change my email or username?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Go to Account Settings and update your email or username. You may be asked to verify your email before changes take effect.
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="topic">
        <h2 class="topic-title">Billing</h2>

        <div class="qa-grid">
            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>Is Museek free?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Museek offers a free tier for basic library and playlist features. Some advanced features may require a paid plan.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>What features are paid?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Paid features can include higher storage limits, premium playback controls, and advanced discovery tools. The exact list is shown on the Pricing page if plans are available.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>How do refunds work?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Refund eligibility depends on your plan and payment provider. If refunds are available, request one from Billing in your account and include your receipt or transaction reference.
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="topic">
        <h2 class="topic-title">Troubleshooting</h2>

        <div class="qa-grid">
            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>The page is stuck on “Loading…”. What should I do?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Refresh the page. If it persists, sign out and sign in again. Try another browser tab, disable extensions, and confirm your network is stable.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>I see an error. How can I report it?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Send a report through Support with steps to reproduce, the page URL, and a screenshot. If you can, include the time it happened and your browser version.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>Which browsers are supported?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Latest Chrome, Edge, Firefox, and Safari. Older versions may work but are not fully tested.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>How do I clear cache and cookies?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    In your browser settings, clear site data for Museek, then reload. If clearing everything is too disruptive, clear only this site’s cookies and cached files.
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="topic">
        <h2 class="topic-title">Contact and support</h2>

        <div class="qa-grid">
            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>How do I contact support?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Use the Contact section in the footer. If your project uses email support, you can also send a message to the support email shown there.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>What information should I include when reporting a bug?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Steps to reproduce, expected vs actual result, screenshots, your device and browser, and the song or playlist name if relevant.
                </div>
            </details>

            <details class="qa">
                <summary>
                    <span>What is your response time?</span>
                    <span class="chev">▾</span>
                </summary>
                <div class="answer">
                    Most messages are answered within 1 to 3 business days. Complex issues may take longer if investigation is needed.
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
